B&B:2000 (http://nces.ed.gov/surveys/B&B/) is a longitudinal survey that examines students\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd education and work experiences as they complete a bachelor\ufffd\ufffd\ufffds degree, with a special emphasis on the experiences of new elementary and secondary teachers. The study was conducted using multiple sources, including institutional records, government databases, and student interviews. B&B:2000 was the first to employ a web-based instrument for collection of institutional records. Postsecondary students and institutions which participated in B&B:2000 were sampled from the 2000 National Postsecondary Student Aid Study (NPSAS:2000). Key statistics produced from B&B:2000 include bachelor\ufffd\ufffd\ufffds degree recipients\ufffd\ufffd\ufffd workforce participation, income and debt repayment, entry into and persistence through graduate school programs, undergraduate experience, demographic backgrounds, expectations regarding graduate study and work, and participation in community service.</dct:description>
